title: First evacuees make way out of Gaza across Rafah border crossing
description: Around 300 foreign citizens and 70 Palestinian medical patients are making their way out of Gaza into Egypt after long negotiations. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez has more details on the release and those, including many Americans, still trapped.

title: Israeli Defense Forces video shows fighting inside Gaza
description: The IDF has released video, edited before circulation and unverified by NBC News, showing military operations by air, land and sea around the Gaza Strip.

title: Surfer's body missing after suspected fatal shark attack in South Australia
description: Emergency services were searching for the body of a surfer in South Australia Wednesday morning after a suspected shark attack, police said.

title: Gunfire and explosions echo around Jenin as Israel stages further raids on the West Bank city
description: Three Palestinians were killed in a Jenin refugee camp in the Israeli-occupied West Bank early Wednesday, officials said. An Israeli military spokesperson said that an aircraft killed several militants.

title: California wildfire, fueled by desert winds, forces evacuations
description: A Southern California wildfire fueled by desert winds burned 2,487 acres and prompted evacuation orders for more than 4,000 people.

title: North Korea closes multiple embassies around the world
description: North Korea is poised to close as many as a dozen embassies, in a move that could see nearly 25 percent of Pyongyang’s missions close worldwide.

title: Saudi Arabia set to host 2034 World Cup after Australia decides not to bid
description: Saudi Arabia looks set to host the 2034 World Cup after Australia, the only other country to show an interest in hosting, decided not to bid.

title: Video shows civilians entering the Rafah crossing to Egypt from Gaza
description: Video from the Rafah crossing between Egypt and the Gaza Strip appeared to show the first time civilians could leave the territory since the start of the Israel-Hamas war.

title: Sen. John Fetterman faces a left-wing backlash over his stance on Israel. He isn't budging.
description: Sen. John Fetterman, D-Pa., usually a reliable progressive voice, is refusing to budge under pressure from the left to back a cease-fire in the Israel-Hamas war.

title: Israeli military releases more video of Gaza Strip ground operation
description: Israel Defense Forces said nine more of its soldiers had died during the ground assault on the Gaza Strip, bringing the total to 11. The news came as further video was released of Israeli forces operating inside the Gaza Strip.
